{"TopicId":196042,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Unify the settings menus","CreatedByName":"coyotesfrontier","CreatedById":181596,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-02T04:43:25Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"coyotesfrontier","CreatedById":181596,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-02T04:43:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP has 3 different settings menus, one for the main menu, one for the space center, and one for flight, each with its own exclusive options. For example, you can only edit navball scale in flight, only edit terrain detail in the main menu, etc. Having them all unified into a single menu would be really nice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-02T05:53:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe problem with this is some settings are save specific, such as difficulty settings.\u00A0 While I agree some items could be consolidated, I don\u0027t think there would be enough to get rid of all but one.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-10T10:35:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe need a PipBoy.\u003Cbr\u003E\nVirtual for Kerbals, real for humans.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221362550149_pip_boy_replica_01.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022600\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022 src=\u0022https://24gadget.ru/uploads/posts/2013-03/1362550149_pip_boy_replica_01.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt could provide the access to the settings and to the simplified ship piloting.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-10T22:11:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223835302\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196042\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221597055747\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe need a PipBoy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know you\u0027re making a joke, but with some of the arduino mods for KSP, making a pip-boy controller for KSP would possibly fall into the \u0022almost trivial\u0022 category.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd how did we get so far off topic in 3 posts?\u00A0\u00A0 Geesh.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-11T13:04:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223830088\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196042\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221596347623\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/2/2020 at 6:53 AM, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe problem with this is some settings are save specific, such as difficulty settings.\u00A0 While I agree some items could be consolidated, I don\u0027t think there would be enough to get rid of all but one.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot like \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E wasn\u0027t referring to the difficulty settings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}